    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-09-19T17:21:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-09-19T17:21:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">745A.00/9–1552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Union of South Africa, at
                            Pretoria</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-09-19T18:21:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1952—6:21 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. During courtesy call on Secy sixteenth<note n="1" xml:id="d544fn1">Memorandum
                        of conversation for this meeting (not printed) is located in Secretary’s
                        Memoranda of Conversation, lot 53 D 344.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HNC1">Havenga</persName> said he understood why it was
                    impossible raise gold price now but was encouraged by trend and believed his
                    view wld eventually prevail in view need for nations to increase monetary
                    reserves. Expressed regret necessity <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss>
                    discrimination US trade in order insure <gloss target="#t_Brit1">Brit</gloss>
                    investment, supply <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss> gold for UK and
                    maintain <gloss target="#t_Brit1">Brit</gloss> market for wine and fruit. Secy
                    said we understood problem but cannot waive on matter of principle though we had
                    not pressed issue. <persName corresp="#p_HNC1">Havenga</persName> gratified Secy
                    assurance early conversion jets <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss>
                    squadron.</p>
                <p>At <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> dinner Secy told <persName
                        corresp="#p_HNC1">Havenga</persName> our concern re effect SoWest Afr issue
                    upon Union’s already strained relations in UN and expressed hope <gloss
                        target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss> cld make some concession. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HNC1">Havenga</persName> receptive and indicated intention use
                    his influence this end. Secy also mentioned hesitancy US investors due
                    uncertainty polit situation but <persName corresp="#p_HNC1">Havenga</persName>
                    unimpressed. <persName>Said</persName> he personally knew major US interests
                    investing <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0981" n="935" xml:id="pg_935"/> and had reassured them on future
                    stability. On basis your advice <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                        65<note n="2" xml:id="d544fn2">Not printed, but see <ref target="#d542fn3"
                            >footnote 3</ref>, <ref target="#pg_928">p. 928</ref>.</note> no direct
                    reference made <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss> domestic crisis. Briefing
                    papers and memo of conversations being airmailed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
